00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,600
Here's what science actually says about old friends hypothesis.

2
00:00:03,600 --> 00:00:09,200
The old friends hypothesis suggests that familiar microbes help our immune system develop better.

3
00:00:09,200 --> 00:00:15,600
Without exposure to these microbes, our immune system might struggle, leading to allergies and autoimmune diseases.

4
00:00:15,600 --> 00:00:21,600
Research shows that kids in rural areas have fewer allergies, possibly from greater microbial diversity.

5
00:00:21,600 --> 00:00:28,800
So, reconnecting with old friends might not just feel good, it could also be vital for our health.

